<br>
Since I've been invited, I guess I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>will</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> say what's on my mind.  I've been fooked over for a long goddam time in pickup groups, and been in groups that fooked over some other poor schlub.  I'm sick of it.  When I lose a roll to someone on a spec, and later that night see them or their bot selling twenty different Spec Spells, it bugs me.  Some of these are the same people that claim NBG is bullshit.  <br>
<br>
Is it fair?  I hate to say it, but yeah it is.  They play (apparently) more than I do, and they work harder.  They deserve to sell their stuff.    Fundamentally I totally agree with Tiff that NBG is abused in some groups, but Greed is also pretty lame.  I disagree that everyone who cries NBG is out to fook ya.  Many are, not all of us. <br>
<br>
You might think I'm trying to be Mr. Nice guy so that I can look good on Xevserver, but ya know something, I'm nice in here because that's who I am-- not because I want to curry favor, but because being a prick is not very satisfying.  Just ask Crylin. <br>
<br>
Look, Dollars to Donuts, I'd lose a flamewar, so there's no need for me to engage in one.  I'll get my ass handed to me, and the point of view I wanted to express is lost in the horrific train wreck of a flood of personal attacks.  All the spectators rubbernecking on the board won't see what I wanted them to see.  If being nice gets the same damn point across, then I'll do it that way.  If that makes me a pansy ass fuck, that's fine.  I'd rather be a &quot;pansy ass fuck&quot; with a point than a loudmouth asshole whose only point is on their head.<br>
<br>
All that said, Tiff, I know <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>you're</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> not calling me out. But if I needed to, I am certain I could take the Gnomeskin gloves off.  I could probably put my mind to it and see who's virtual rant jaw gets ripped off, cracked in half and then one part shoved down their throat and the other half up their arse.  <br>
<br>
And then, the next night, I'll group with the same person I ripped, and ask them if they want to roll on that spec that dropped.   Because I know its the fair thing-- the RIGHT thing to do. But I will also let it be known that I do, in fact, need several spells.  And the other guy will win the roll, because they always do, and put it up for sale for 50K in the Bazaar.  <p>Hi, my name is Gundark, and I'm an alchemyholic.<br>
